revision.text:
{{unsourced|date=October 2010}}
'''Abubus''', also spelt '''Abobus''' or '''Abobi''', was the father of [[Ptolemy (son of Abubus)|Ptolemy]]. He is mentioned only in the [[1 Maccabees|first book of the Maccabees]] {{bibleverse-nb|1|Maccabees|16:11|NAB}} and {{bibleverse-nb|1|Maccabees|16:15|NAB}}, wherein Ptolemy invites [[Simon Maccabaeus]] and his two sons, Mattathias and Judas, to a banquet, subsequently killing them.

==External links==
* [http://biblehub.com/topical/a/abubus.htm Abubus], ''International Standard Bible Encyclopedia'' at BibleHub.com

