{{Infobox cemetery | name = Cementerio Israelita de La Paz | image = | imagesize = 280px | caption = | map_type = | map_size = | map_caption = | established = 1917 | country = {{URU}} | location = [[La Paz, Canelones|La Paz]], [[Canelones Department|Canelones]] | coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|45.50185|-73.65471|display=inline,title}} --> | latitude = | longitude = | type = [[Jewish cemetery|Jewish]] | owner = | size = | graves = | website = | findagrave = | political = }} The '''Israelite Cemetery''' ({{lang-es|'''Cementerio Israelita'''}}) '''of [[La Paz, Canelones|La Paz]]''' is the only [[Jewish cemetery]] in Uruguay. It was established November 28, 1917.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cciu.org.uy/news_detail.php?id=4450|title=The first 2 tombs in La Paz|accessdate=28 February 2012 |publisher=CCIU}} {{es icon}}</ref> There are sections dedicated to Jews of different origins: [[Sephardi Jews|Sephardim]], Hungarian, German, [[Ashkenazi Jews|Ashkenazim]], etc.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jai.com.uy/?Q=articulo&ID=176 |title=Jewish funerals in Uruguay |accessdate=24 March 2014 |publisher=Jai.com.uy }} {{es icon}}</ref>
In 2014, [[QR code]]s were being implemented for its tombstones, in order to enable web access to images and location data for every tomb there. It is claimed to be the first cemetery in the world to have introduced this innovation.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.elpais.com.uy/informacion/cementerio-judio-se-moderniza-codigos.html |title=Uruguayan Jewish Cemetery QRfied |date=24 March 2014 |publisher=[[El País (Uruguay)|EL PAIS]] }} {{es icon}}</ref>
