 | poly_wives          = 10
 | poly_notes          = ''The Seer'' was a periodical published to defend the LDS Church's practice of polygamy. Despite [[William Clayton (Mormon)|William Clayton]] claiming in his journal, first published in 1921, that she had been told of the revelation on polygamy on July 12, 1843,<ref>Journal of William Clayton - excerpts online at http://www.geocities.com/Athens/Delphi/3750/Clayton_intro.html {{Verify credibility|date=August 2008}}</ref> [[Emma Smith]], Joseph Smith's widow, claimed that the very first time she ever became aware of polygamy being attributed to her late husband was 10 years later when she read about it in Pratt's ''The Seer'' in 1853.<ref>''Saints' Herald'' 65:1044–1045</ref>
